is.na()

data[!complete.cases(data),] list rows of data that have missing values

newdata <- na.omit(data) create new dataset without missing data

na.omit() omit all rows containing missing values.

data <- c(12, 4, 6, NA, 45, NA,99)
is.na(data) #NA
## [1] FALSE FALSE FALSE  TRUE FALSE  TRUE FALSE
which(is.na(data)) #NA
## [1] 4 6
sum(is.na(data)) #NA
## [1] 2
mean(data) #NA
## [1] NA
mean(data, na.rm = TRUE) #NA
## [1] 33.2
data[is.na(data)] <- mean(data, na.rm = TRUE) #NAmean
data
## [1] 12.0  4.0  6.0 33.2 45.0 33.2 99.0
data[data == 99] <- NA #99NA
data
## [1] 12.0  4.0  6.0 33.2 45.0 33.2   NA
